217 (iii) Prior occurrences of substantially similar wrongful conduct by the third person
218 whose wrongful conduct caused the injury, if the owner or occupier knew such third
219 person was or would be upon the premises and knew of such prior occurrences of
220 substantially similar wrongful conduct;
221 (2) The injury sustained by the invitee was a reasonably foreseeable consequence of such
222 wrongful conduct by a third person;
223 (3) Such wrongful conduct by a third person was a reasonably foreseeable consequence
224 of such third person exploiting a specific physical condition of the premises known to the
225 owner or occupier, which created a reasonably foreseeable risk of wrongful conduct on
