304 In any action for negligent security:
305 (1) If the trier of fact finds that any defendant is liable to the plaintiff, the trier of fact
306 shall make an apportionment of fault under Code Section 51-12-33, and in making such
307 an apportionment, the trier of fact shall reasonably apportion fault to:
308 (A) The owner or occupier;
309 (B) Any third person whose wrongful conduct was a cause of the injury from which
310 the claim of negligent security arises; and
311 (C) Any other persons to whom fault otherwise should be apportioned under Code
312 Section 51-12-33;
313 (2) In connection with an apportionment of fault under Code Section 51-12-33, no party
314 shall offer evidence, or make an argument or other comment in the hearing of any juror
315 or prospective juror, concerning:
