316 (A) Any sentence of imprisonment or probation, fine, or other punishment that has
317 been, or could be, imposed in a criminal prosecution of any third person for the
318 wrongful conduct from which the claim of negligent security arises;
319 (B) The financial resources of any party or nonparty; or
320 (C) The effect of an apportionment of fault upon any award of damages to the plaintiff;
321 and
322 (3) If a jury fails as the trier of fact to apportion a reasonable degree of fault to the third
323 person whose wrongful conduct was a cause of the injury from which the claim of
324 negligent security arises, the trial court shall set aside the verdict of the jury and order a
