342 SECTION 7.
343 Said title is further amended in Article 1 of Chapter 12, relating to general provisions relative
344 to damages, by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
345 "51-12-1.1.
346 (a) In any civil action to recover damages resulting from injury or death to a person,
347 special damages for medical and healthcare expenses shall be recoverable only as provided
348 in this Code section.
349 (b) Special damages for medical and healthcare expenses shall be limited to the expenses
350 of medically necessary care, treatment, or services, and the amount of such special
351 damages shall be limited to:
352 (1) Amounts paid by or on behalf of the plaintiff to healthcare providers for reasonable
353 and customary care, treatment, or services;
354 (2) Amounts necessary to satisfy the incurred but unpaid charges for reasonable and
355 customary care, treatment, or services due from the plaintiff or a third party on behalf of
356 the plaintiff; and
357 (3) With respect to medical and healthcare expenses not yet incurred, such amounts as
358 are actually necessary to satisfy future charges for medically necessary care, treatment,
359 or services.
360 (c) If the plaintiff in any such civil action has any form of public or private health
361 insurance, including benefits under a governmental workers' compensation program,
362 charges for medically necessary care, treatment, or services under paragraph (2) or (3) of
363 subsection (b) of this Code section shall be the amount by which such charges may be
364 satisfied by the claimant's health insurance in addition to the amount representing the
365 plaintiff's responsibility for the portion of the charges under the insurance contract or
366 applicable governmental program, regardless of whether the health insurance has been
367 used, is used, or will be used to satisfy the charges.
- 15 -

25 LC 49 2233-ECS
368 (d) If the trier of fact renders a verdict awarding any damages pursuant to subsection (b)
369 of this Code section, and if the plaintiff's charges for medically necessary care, treatment,
370 or services were satisfied in full or in part by any form of public or private health insurance
371 for which the plaintiff paid one or more premiums, upon submission by the plaintiff of
372 documentation demonstrating the payment of such premiums within 30 days of the date of
373 the verdict, the court shall add to the verdict the cost of such premiums for each month in
374 which such damages were incurred from the month of the incident giving rise to the action
375 until the earlier of:
376 (1) The final treatment for the plaintiff's injuries for which such damages were awarded
377 pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code section; or
378 (2) The conclusion of the trial.
379 (e) The premium costs reimbursed pursuant to subsection (d) of this Code section shall not
380 exceed the damages awarded pursuant to subsection (b) of this Code section that were
381 incurred in the corresponding month.
382 (f) If the court provides for the recovery of premium costs pursuant to subsection (d) of
383 this Code section, the defendant shall have 15 days to petition the court to review the
384 accuracy of such premium costs before judgment is entered.
385 (g) Nothing in this Code section shall be construed to limit the right of a plaintiff or
386 defendant to present evidence or testimony, or both, challenging the reasonableness of
387 medical and healthcare expenses, whether incurred or projected future expenses, or the
